# Skill Execution Guardrails

- Treat `*-meta` skills as analysis-only: no file edits, no command execution.
- Use `*-execution` skills for implementation/verification work.
- Default to human-readable responses for normal interactive work.
- Use strict JSON only when machine-consumable output is needed (loops, verification pipelines, batch automation) or explicitly required by the active skill.
- For debug loops, apply one minimal fix per iteration with hypothesis + verification.
- For verification, never claim success if required checks were not run.
- Never commit unless the user explicitly asks.
- Use `skill-creator` only when the user explicitly asks to create/edit a skill.
